result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexander C. Klebenow was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Sex Registry Violation, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 301.45(6)(a)1.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Alexander C. Klebenow in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Alexander C. Klebenow in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement.  Atty Hendee states that both parties are waiving the right for a PSI.  Atty Gumz agrees.  Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made freely, voluntarily & Intelligently.  Court relies on the criminal complaint for a factual basis.  

BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty.

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.
Atty Gumz makes sentencing arguments. Atty Gumz waives the right for a PSI.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  Withhold Sentence; 36 months Probation with conditions:
Court Costs = $268.00
Comply with any and all counseling recommended by the Agent
Comply with Sex Offender Registry
DNA Sample + $250.00 Surcharge
Pay costs within his probationary period and will be set up through the Agent
No PSI will be ordered.
